description.en:
The topic of the presentation is related to experimental psychology.
The topic of the presentation is one of the following (but preferably A):
a) an introduction of the student's own research (either in the planning, conducting or completed phase);
b) an overview of the theoretical background of the student's research topic with the aim to set research questions and/or hypotheses;
c) an overview of a current important problem or topic in experimental psychology based on literature (in case the student doesn't have her/his own research topic and in a prior agreement with the lecturer).
The presentation is given orally, preferably with accompanying visual material (e.g. slideshow).
